name: r-slider
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.2.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-slider
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/slider_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/slider/slider_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a35537604bf7065594e0f23fec403c0272dd992cf92329e2647ceb31d812b3ef

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-glue
    - r-rlang >=0.4.5
    - r-vctrs >=0.2.4
    - r-warp
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-glue
    - r-rlang >=0.4.5
    - r-vctrs >=0.2.4
    - r-warp

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('slider')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('slider')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/DavisVaughan/slider
  license: MIT
  summary: Provides type-stable rolling window functions over any R data type. Cumulative and expanding windows are also supported. For more advanced usage, an index can be used as a secondary vector that defines how sliding windows are to be created.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mxr-conda
    - conda-forge/r
    - oblute
    - rluria14
